claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A table showing pre‐ and post‐vaccination geometric mean titers (with 95% confidence intervals) and percentage seroresponse (4‐fold rise to ≥1:40) for placebo, Flublok, previously vaccinated Flublok subgroup, and non-previously vaccinated Flublok subgroup across three influenza strains. does not support the claim: the table presents immunogenicity outcomes but provides no information on the antigen content of Flublok versus standard‐dose vaccines, and no 3× HA dose comparison is shown. Note: None
